{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "The Day of the Lord"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"Now about the times and seasons, brothers, we do not need to write to you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"For you are fully aware that the Day of the Lord will come like a thief in the night."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"While people are saying,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Peace and security,",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "destruction will come upon them suddenly, like labor pains on a pregnant woman, and they will not escape."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"But you, brothers, are not in the darkness so that this day should overtake you like a thief."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"For you are all sons of the light and sons of the day; we do not belong to the night or to the darkness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"So then, let us not sleep as the others do, but let us remain awake and sober."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"For those who sleep, sleep at night; and those who get drunk, get drunk at night."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"But since we belong to the day, let us be sober, putting on the breastplate of faith and love, and the helmet of our hope of salvation."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"For God has not appointed us to suffer wrath, but to obtain salvation through our Lord Jesus Christ."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"He died for us so that, whether we are awake or asleep, we may live together with Him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"Therefore encourage and build one another up, just as you are already doing."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Christian Living"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"But we ask you, brothers, to acknowledge those who work diligently among you, who preside over you in the Lord and give you instruction."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"In love, hold them in highest regard because of their work. Live in peace with one another."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"And we urge you, brothers, to admonish the unruly, encourage the fainthearted, help the weak, and be patient with everyone."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"Make sure that no one repays evil for evil. Always pursue what is good for one another and for all people."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"Rejoice at all times."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"Pray without ceasing."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"Give thanks in every circumstance, for this is God’s will for you in Christ Jesus."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"Do not extinguish the Spirit."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"Do not treat prophecies with contempt,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"but test all things. Hold fast to what is good."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"Abstain from every form of evil."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Final Blessings and Instructions"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"Now may the God of peace Himself sanctify you completely, and may your entire spirit, soul, and body be kept blameless[^10] at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"The One who calls you is faithful, and He will do it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"Brothers, pray for us as well."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"Greet all the brothers with a holy kiss."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"I charge you before the Lord to have this letter read to all the brothers."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "\"The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.[^11]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}